; Regression test for issue #1638: Selinger's multiple currency accounting & ledger (BZ#566)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1638
;
; Peter Selinger's multiple currency accounting method requires that double-entry
; consistency holds across currency exchanges: buying a foreign currency at one
; rate and selling it at another should properly track the realized gain/loss.
;
; The key test: buying EUR at $1.20, selling some at $1.30, should show:
; - Correct USD balance reflecting actual cash flows
; - Correct market value including gain on remaining holdings

P 2010/01/01 EUR $1.20
P 2010/07/01 EUR $1.30

; Buy 100 EUR at $1.20/EUR (total cost: $120)
2010/01/01 Buy EUR
    Assets:EUR           100 EUR @ $1.20
    Assets:USD          -$120

; Sell 50 EUR at $1.30/EUR (proceeds: $65, realized gain: $5)
2010/07/01 Sell EUR
    Assets:USD            $65
    Assets:EUR           -50 EUR @ $1.30

test bal
             $-55.00
              50 EUR  Assets
              50 EUR    EUR
             $-55.00    USD
--------------------
             $-55.00
              50 EUR
end test

test bal -V --now 2010/08/01
              $10.00  Assets
              $65.00    EUR
             $-55.00    USD
--------------------
              $10.00
end test
